// RULE (NOT yet enforced — EXPECTED TO FAIL until it is):
//   The stdlib modules are proc/func libraries with no `.i.arche` contract, so they are NOT devices.
//   A driver must not be able to `#import { net }` (or fmt, io, str, …) until they are restructured
//   as devices with declared interfaces. `net` in particular exposes a top-level public
//   `socket :: opaque` from its implementation file with no contract — exactly what this forbids.
//
// Today `#import { net }` succeeds, so the grep finds no error and the test FAILS.
// RUN: %arche build -o %t %s > %t.out 2>&1 ; grep -qiE "not a device|only devices|no datasheet|no interface|is not a device" %t.out
#import { net }

main :: proc() {
  net.listen(8080)(s:);
}
